train and val have images after inversion correction

How to Run

Step 1

make sure best_lung_model.h5 is in the same folder

use segment_v1.py to generate new dataset with segmentations performed
after execution new folder train-segmented and val-segmented will be created

(Used H100 with 10 GB memory)

rename train-segmented to train and val-segmented to val

Step 2

run model_v1.py

bash command : 

python model_v1.py --models swin_t
python model_v1.py --models convnext_t

Step 3 :

Take a random image from train or val and pass it to predict.py

bash command: 

python predict.py --image <enter_image_name>.jpg --model checkpoints/swin_t_
best.pt --device cuda

python predict.py --image <enter_image_name>.jpg --model checkpoints/convnext_t_
best.pt --device cuda

Note: 

segment_v0.py make the background black via lung detection and bounding box
segment_v1.py makes applies soft masking ( dims non lung regions) via lung detection and bounding box

Run train_laf.py

python train_laf.py --train-dir tb-data-softmasked/train --val-dir tb-data-softmasked/val --output-dir checkpoints --models swin_t convnext_t --img-size 512 --use-laf --use-alignnorm --epochs 12 --batch-size 16 --use-preprocessing --laf-kernel-size1 3 --laf-kernel-size2 7
